LDAP Maven Plugin

  This plugin provides the goals to:

  * Load records into or dump records from an LDAP directory. Records can be dumped to
    {{{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LDIF}LDIF}} or
    {{{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Directory_Service_Markup_Language}DSML}} formats.

  * Launch and shutdown one of the following embedded directory server within the Maven build life-cycle:

    * {{{http://directory.apache.org/apacheds/}ApacheDS}}

    * {{{http://opendj.forgerock.org/}OpenDJ}}

    * {{{https://www.unboundid.com/products/directory-server.php}UnboundID}}


* Goals Overview

~~  General Information about the goals.

  * {{{./ldap-maven-plugin/load-mojo.html}ldap:load}} Load directory entries from DSML or LDIF format.

  * {{{./ldap-maven-plugin/dump-mojo.html}ldap:dump}} Dump directory entries to DSML LDIF format.

  * {{{./ldap-maven-plugin/run-mojo.html}ldap:run}} Run an embedded ApacheDS server.

  * {{{./ldap-maven-plugin/stop-mojo.html}ldap:stop}} Stop an embedded ApacheDS server.

